title: Most City of Industry council members work for the city’s highest paid contractors
text: When former Industry Councilman Jeff Parriott lost his $88, 000 job with the city’s redevelopment agency, he switched from coordinating Industry’s development projects to archiving historical photographs at the city-owned Homestead Museum .
